reviews.text: Rooms are OK only for sleep,  try to watch TV, too much noise all the time,  specially in the morning.   Buffet Dinner is same all  the time,  they just enjoying in chicken...staff are friendly. WiFi slow
My father visting last 2 nights.Happy experience in d service

Breakfast is not that good, the dinner menu is even worse and overpriced tastes like everything is frozen microwave food. Today I came back to the room at 18:00 and it wasn't cleaned. The machines at the gym are old. The room I am in you can hear dogs barking all night.
Nice hotel with good service. Recommended
Great Hotel Suggestion to all indian Stay Here

The food was extraordinary. Absolutely delicious. Alcohol is also served. Great list of wines and beer. The service is prompt. Very clean and one of the most amazing views in Alexandria. Takes you back in time where traces of cosmopolitan Alexandria are more than just obvious. The decoration is fantastic. Prices are high, but you get what you pay for.

Would never hesitate to rate this restaurant as "perfect" and give it 10 stars
The staff are super nice, food is yummy and the venue is cosy
Expensive but deserves each pound
Highly recommended
Perfect place for lunch and dinner.
Great place for shisha
Very good decorations and food, yet it's a before sunset restaurant. It's problem is about the lack of variety in hot drinks and it's extremely high prices.

Good cozy place. I’m not impressed by their crepes, to be honest. The crepes don’t have its own flavor and sometimes weird combinations of flavors in general. Since I love France very much, but didn’t really met here something similar to what I had in France, maybe because of local ingredients, but still

Wonderful big crepes, especially the dinner ones. I am not too crazy about the selection of French wines ( I prefer  American wine). I love, love the ambiance, especially in the summer, when the outside is open. It is a must for Bastille day, they have roaming musicians!

One of my favorite restaurants in the area! The food is authentic and the portions are a great size. They have  something for everyone. Every time I go I try something new and have never been disappointed. The staff is just as great as the food, so kind and friendly.
So tasty.  Substantial savory crepes, too.  Not like the ones that are rolled up like a flute, with not enough filling.  These are big and square with lots of filling.   Mmmmm

I think this might be the first french crêperie in Chicago. If not, it's definitely the best. I actually went to check out the French onion soup (ITS AMAZING HERE MUST GET IT!) I don't really like sweets, but the server gave both my gf and I free crepes for our anniversary and oh my lord I was instantly converted into a crepe lover. This place is very charming, has amazing service and a warm energy. Must check it out!

Love walking into a Starbucks and smelling the fresh coffee. This location was clean and the staff friendly. Coffee was made to order and correctly made for this picky coffee drinker lol. This spot has an area for when you are wanting to socialize or break out the computer/books and do some studying while sipping on a latte. Only problem I seen was the drive through and parking area are very tight but couldn't take a star away just for that. Keep it up at this location cause my little girl and I will definitely be back for our coffee.
Always fast, friendly, and informative! Their coffee is great and their snacks are always yummy! Mobile pickup through their app is always very convenient as well!

Yummy but prices need to stop going up, they  are beyond being a very successful business that has millions of people addicted and stopping for ine of their many yummy beverages and foods almost every day like its crack, stop being greedy with the cost increase of everything, PLEASE. I want to be able to afford my coffee "crack" lol just playing, kinda. Attention there's no illegal drugs served at any Starbucks facility
... that I'm aware of!
Very friendly service. Got the order correct. Fast.
Rude, impersonal staff, slow service, dirty restrooms. The food is blah, you get better quality food at much lower prices at McDonalds or any of the other fast food chains in the area.

I enjoy shopping at the Farmer's Market. Pleasant outdoor, natural environment. Friendly people make the experience a little different and better than the usual shopping trip. Nice for a little change. Eat fresher produce while supporting local farmers.
Its an awesome park! I love walking there its beautiful! Plus its not that far from where i live. So only walk in total 2 miles one to the park and one mile back home. 5 stars definitely
LOVE the dog park! The people are friendly and my dogs have a great time!
A nice park albeit a bit on the dirty side. It would be really nice if it were cleaned up. Baseball fields and other amenities. Porta-pottys available that aren't too horrible.

Not to good. It has soccer fields baseball fields and a dog park. Its soccer fields are poorly maintained and the ball always randomly bounces because of bumps. The base ball fields there ok but could be a bit better and the only good thing is the dog park in the back because its dogs (no offense cats). Trying to get through traffic on the road is hard and parking is pretty bad.
One of my preferred locations for delicious Quality Meals. You won't be disappointed in the menu and service. The service here is attentive. They have a lot of positive reviews for a reason.
Great location for quality Quality Meals. service is always timely even when they have a full house. the staff was helpful and kind. this place has an awesome atmosphere.
quality meals at this location - very good. staff is always timely even when they have a full house. the service was very friendly and kind. this place has a nice atmosphere.
Service was excellent..Very nice and relaxing ambiance. Food needed a little more temperature. My pork meat was almost room temp. Good selection of wines and martinis...

My wife and I celebrated our 48th anniversary here tonight and it was truly an unforgettable experience!  Christian, our server, was there any time we needed him without being in the way.

We started our meal with a brie and prosciutto appetizer and  we each had a salad with brie and bacon, along with greens.

She had tenderloin medallions and I had the beef tenderloin.  We finished all this off with creme brulee.  I'm still full!

All the food was above our expectations!  We are already planning our next anniversary there.

Add-on for a year later.  Went back there for Valentines Day, had the same server, Christian,  and nothing had changed.  The food is superb, the service was top drawer and we love it!

Imagine fighting your way through winter storm, 100 km on foot. You had to fight your way through a pack of savage penguins and their boss leader, the polar bear, to the bitter end. You open the door after all your struggle into an oasis ice cream, awful awfuls, and traditional American fare. You think you were safe...but in the shadows a monster lurks. You let your guard down, and you order your food happy and content ...but the feeling that something is watching you slowly creeps down your spine. The monster exposes itself as a manager that has an attitude of the most heinous creature in all the land. Your Oasis is ruined... On top of this they have some how figured out how to take flavor out of food and replace it with salt/grease.

This was basically my experience with this Newport creamery. The ice cream was good but the manager at this location it's probably the worst person in customer service I've ever experienced in New England... You can tell the staff is unorganized because of her toxic leadership. I strongly recommend restructuring your management group to better facilitate a well running and friendly staff.

2 stars for quality ice cream though...
Slow staff,  burger was overcooked and dry fries were cold.  Manager did not care.  Will never come here again.

Newport Creamery is a decent place with average food but good people.  We go there mainly for breakfast because it's local, fast, hot, inexpensive, and filling.  That being said, the quality of ingredients is average, not bad but not impressive.  Basically it's an ice cream shop with a diner attached, that de-emphasized their ice cream.  IMHO, they are doing too many things to do anything really well.  It's decent enough food at a decent price, and you can take the kids.
Had our first Big Beef the Creamery Way in over 16 yes & it was like really coming home, DELISH!!
Always great! Servers are wonderful.

Food is okay. But some of their plates are overpriced for the volume of food you're getting. Someone in my group ordered a beef vinegar hot pot which was actually of good value and taste. Otherwise it's relatively disappointing. Live music is nice. Service is correct.
Expensive. Staff forced us to order extra dishes using very bad attitude! Only recommend this if you want to be ripped off and treated badly.
Beautiful decoration and friendly service. Food is fresh and delicious. Live traditional music and dance along the meal. Worth trying!
Fine food, slow server
Enjoyed the atmosphere and the food.
